<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>1. Your complete signature file should not exceed 30kb in size.<br>
2. Keep the physical size of your signature to a decent size. Common banner-ad sizing (468x60 pixels) is a good example of an appropriate physical size.<br>
3. Only post your custom signature once per thread. If you are posting a second time in a thread, uncheck the &quot;Include custom signature&quot; box before clicking on the 'Post' button.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
As long as they conform to these three simple rules everything should be fine. The problem is when people don't follow the overly simple rules...<br>
<br>
Thing is, of the sigs posted in this thread - every single one without exception is bigger than the recommended size (468 pixels wide, 60 pixels high).<br>
<br>
Six sigs are larger than the recommended size of 30kb, one as freaking huge as 300kb, jebus.<br>
<br>
Two posters posted their sig 3 times in this very thread.<br>
<br>
If people can't follow rules, why do we have any at all? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=myztic>MyztiC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>Born-Again Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 836<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/15/03 5:16:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25697.topic&index=44>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Those sig pics...</span><hr size=1> Because the rules are too complicated to some people, it would be easier to turn off the sigs for whole board. But I guess it is more trendy to break the rules and then call people who don't like it 'nazis'. *sigh* Oh well, since mods have too much to do with jihads and other kind of crap, to actually enforce the forum rules, maybe we as forum users so adhere by them, or maybe the mods should make such rules that they would be adhered to automatically.<br>
